Shimao Property Said to Hire Banks For $500 Million 7-Year Bonds

-- B y   K a t r i n a   N i c h o l a s
-- 
2011-03-01T01:24:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/shimao-property-said-to-hire-banks-for-500-million-7-year-bonds.html
  Shimao Property Holdings Ltd . hired
Standard Chartered Plc and Morgan Stanley to help it sell as
much as $500 million of seven-year bonds, according to two
people familiar with the matter.  Proceeds from the sale will be used to refinance floating-
rate notes maturing this year and to finance development
projects, one of the people said, asking not to be identified as
details are private. The notes may be sold as early as today,
the person said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Katrina Nicholas at 
 knicholas2@bloomberg.net  